    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Stelis ligulata are quercetin, kaempferol, flavonoids, epicatechin, and apigenin. These bioactive compounds exhibit strong antioxidant properties, attributed to their ability to scavenge free radicals and reduce oxidative stress. Quercetin, a key flavonoid, has been shown to inhibit inflammatory responses and modulate immune function, while kaempferol has been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties. Epicatechin, a flavonoid with notable neuroprotective effects, has been found to improve cognitive function and reduce the risk of neurodegenerative diseases. Apigenin, a flavonoid with anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties, has been shown to inhibit the growth of cancer cells and induce apoptosis, making Stelis ligulata a valuable source of natural compounds for therapeutic applications.",
