    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Stelis ligulata are derived from its leaves and flowers, which are rich in flavonoids and phenolic acids. Tea and infusion of the leaves are used to treat fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues due to their anti-inflammatory properties. Tincture preparations are made by extracting the flavonoids and phenolic acids from the flowers and leaves, which are used to treat respiratory issues and allergies. A salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in oil to treat skin issues such as wounds, eczema, and acne due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. Decoction of the roots is used to treat gastrointestinal issues such as diarrhea and stomach ulcers due to its antispasmodic properties.",
