    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Stelis ligulata improperly include experiencing nausea, which is caused by the ingestion of toxic compounds found in the plant, particularly the presence of cardenolides and bufadienolides. Developing an allergic reaction to Stelis ligulata can also occur, resulting in symptoms such as hives, itching, and swelling, due to the plant's sap or other chemical compounds. Improper use of Stelis ligulata can induce vomiting, a response of the body to eliminate the toxic substances, and cause diarrhea, as the body attempts to rid itself of the toxins. Additionally, headache can be a symptom of Stelis ligulata poisoning, resulting from the plant's toxic compounds affecting the nervous system. These side effects can be severe and potentially life-threatening, especially if medical attention is not sought promptly.",
    "uses": "Stelis ligulata is reported to have various medicinal properties and uses, although more research is needed to confirm its effectiveness. Some traditional healers use the plant to treat respiratory issues, such as bronchitis and asthma. The plant's leaves and stems are said to have anti-inflammatory properties, which may help alleviate pain and reduce swelling. In addition, Stelis ligulata is believed to have antimicrobial properties, which could aid in the treatment of infections. More studies are necessary to fully understand the plant's medicinal uses and potential benefits.",
    "taxonomy": "Stelis ligulata is a species of orchid in the subtribe Stanhopeinae. It belongs to the family Orchidaceae and the genus Stelis. The classification of Stelis ligulata further includes the tribe Cranichideae and the order Asparagales. This orchid species is native to Central America, specifically Costa Rica and Panama. The exact classification may vary depending on the source and ongoing research in the field of botany.",
    "benefits": "Stelis ligulata has been found to have potential health benefits due to its rich antioxidant properties. It is said to have anti-inflammatory properties which can help in reducing pain and swelling. The plant is also believed to have antimicrobial properties that can aid in fighting infections. Stelis ligulata has been studied for its possible use in treating various health issues such as diabetes and heart diseases. Further research is needed to confirm its efficacy in providing these benefits.",
    "parts": "Stelis ligulata is a species of orchid, and like many orchids, its parts may have been used in traditional medicine. However, specific information on the medicinal parts of Stelis ligulata is not readily available. Further research is needed to determine the potential medicinal uses of this species. The flowers and leaves of many orchids have been used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments. In general, the medicinal properties of orchids can vary widely depending on the species and specific compounds present.",
    "intro": "Stelis ligulata, also known as Ligulate Stelis, is a species of orchid native to the tropical regions of Central America. This plant has been traditionally used in herbal medicine to treat various health issues, including digestive problems and fever, due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The bioactive constituents of Stelis ligulata include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic acids, which are responsible for its medicinal effects. In herbal medicine, Stelis ligulata is commonly prepared as a tea or tincture to treat digestive issues, and is also used in traditional remedies for colds and flu."
